101
00:08:53,369 --> 00:08:55,566
I'm sure everyone here knows that word.

102
00:08:56,196 --> 00:08:59,371
It's dusk. A time when it's neither day nor night.

103
00:08:59,929 --> 00:09:01,800
When the border between worlds blur,

104
00:09:02,079 --> 00:09:04,638
and one might encounter something not human.

105
00:09:05,913 --> 00:09:09,335
Another older term for it is "dusk-light."

106
00:09:09,675 --> 00:09:12,683
Some people also call it "golden hour."

107
00:09:12,836 --> 00:09:13,989
What about magic hour?

108
00:09:14,026 --> 00:09:15,703
It's something my grandma says.

109
00:09:15,796 --> 00:09:19,251
Well, golden hour and magic hour are technically the same.

110
00:09:19,336 --> 00:09:22,019
But it's a term that mostly photographers use.

111
00:09:22,596 --> 00:09:25,190
Well, she does take a lot of pictures.

112
00:09:27,516 --> 00:09:30,080
