That's why I've hand-picked some links
below to help you out, you wall flower.

536
00:39:35,447 --> 00:39:36,108
For real?

537
00:39:43,730 --> 00:39:45,503
She's making fun of me.

538
00:40:14,743 --> 00:40:16,220
You know something, Taki?

539
00:40:17,072 --> 00:40:20,628
Today you're... you're like a different person.

540
00:40:29,884 --> 00:40:31,246
Um, Miss Okudera,

541
00:40:31,926 --> 00:40:34,910
You getting hungry? We could get dinner.

542
00:40:36,641 --> 00:40:38,286
Uh. Let's call it a day.

543
00:40:40,057 --> 00:40:40,968
All right.

544
00:40:41,474 --> 00:40:42,781
I could be wrong,

545
00:40:43,327 --> 00:40:44,843
and I'm sorry if I am.

546
00:40:44,983 --> 00:40:45,694
About?

547
00:40:45,954 --> 00:40:49,568
But you used to have a little crush on me, am I right?

548
00:40:51,237 --> 00:40:54,207
But right now, there's someone else you like, huh?

549
00:40:54,642 --> 00:40:57,937
No. No, it's not that.

550
00:40:58,006 --> 00:40:58,876
Really?

551
00:40:59,143 --> 00:41:01,585
There's no one. It's not like that.

552
00:41:01,671 --> 00:41:03,404
Are you sure about that?

553
00:41:04,866 --> 00:41:08,089
Well, thanks for today! See you at work.

554
00:41:23,164 --> 00:41:24,924
By the time the date's over...

555
00:41:25,169 --> 00:41:27,829
...you should be able to see the comet in the sky.

556
00:41:31,470 --> 00:41:33,773
What does she mean? Weirdo.

557
00:42:02,483 --> 00:42:04,503
Oh, it's you, Teshi.

558
00:42:05,676 --> 00:42:06,143
No,

559
00:42:06,607 --> 00:42:09,612
I just didn't feel like going, that's all. I'm fine.

560
00:42:10,846 --> 00:42:12,924
What? The festival?

561
00:42:15,802 --> 00:42:17,203
Oh, yeah, the comet.

562
00:42:17,635 --> 00:42:19,467
It'll be at its brightest today, right?

563
00:42:20,964 --> 00:42:23,785
Okay, got it. See ya later.

564
00:42:27,368 --> 00:42:31,006
You're just looking forward to
seeing Mitsuha in a yukata, aren'tcha?

565
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:32,214
I-I am not!

566
00:42:32,664 --> 00:42:34,735
I mean, it didn't even cross my mind.

567
00:42:35,746 --> 00:42:39,004
Y'know, she sounded kinda down when I talked to her.

568
00:42:39,063 --> 00:42:41,122
Maybe she just didn't want a call from ya.

569
00:42:41,147 --> 00:42:42,396
It's not funny!

570
00:42:42,451 --> 00:42:43,171
Sorry to keep ya.

571
00:42:43,402 --> 00:42:44,033
Oh, she's here!

572
00:42:44,058 --> 00:42:44,519
You're late.

573
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:49,994
Mitsuha, what happened to...?

574
00:42:51,457 --> 00:42:52,580
Your hair!

575
00:42:53,369 --> 00:42:55,959
I guess... it's weird.

576
00:43:05,170 --> 00:43:06,983
You think it's gotta do with some guy?

577
00:43:07,008 --> 00:43:08,450
Like... he broke her heart?

578
00:43:08,525 --> 00:43:11,406
Guys always just assume that it has to do with a boy.

579
00:43:11,820 --> 00:43:13,943
She said she felt like cutting it.

580
00:43:13,975 --> 00:43:17,761
Ya sure about that? You really think
she felt like cutting off that much of it?

581
00:43:18,751 --> 00:43:20,484
Hey, guys! I can see it!

582
00:43:39,085 --> 00:43:40,751
Whoa.

583
00:43:59,488 --> 00:44:03,068
The number you are trying to reach is
currently outside the cellular network

584
00:44:03,093 --> 00:44:04,532
or has been turned off due...

585
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:11,225
I'll just have to tell her how lousy
the date ended up the next time we switch.

586
00:44:12,526 --> 00:44:13,599
That's what I thought.

587
00:44:14,889 --> 00:44:15,278
But...

588
00:44:16,071 --> 00:44:20,446
For some reason, the switches Mitsuha
and I'd been going through until now...

589
00:44:21,844 --> 00:44:23,193
they never happened again.

590
00:46:16,415 --> 00:46:16,870
Wha...?

591
00:46:17,758 --> 00:46:20,438
What're...? What're you doing here?

592
00:46:23,877 --> 00:46:26,171
Tsukasa told me about it, so here I am.

593
00:46:30,042 --> 00:46:31,495
I asked for two things.

594
00:46:31,955 --> 00:46:35,142
To cover my shift, and to back
up my alibi if my dad asked.

595
00:46:35,167 --> 00:46:36,988
Relax, Takagi's gonna take your shift.

596
00:46:37,144 --> 00:46:39,961
Gotcha covered! But you owe me dinner!

597
00:46:40,280 --> 00:46:41,928
So you're all in on it.

598
00:46:42,129 --> 00:46:43,862
You've got everyone worried about you.

599
00:46:43,887 --> 00:46:44,384
Huh?

600
00:46:44,711 --> 00:46:47,850
We can't ignore this. What if
somebody's trying to pull one over on you?

601
00:46:47,877 --> 00:46:48,863
Like catfish?

602
00:46:49,143 --> 00:46:51,407
I mean you met this person online, didn't you?

603
00:46:51,432 --> 00:46:53,778
No, not exactly! It's kinda complicated.

604
00:46:53,802 --> 00:46:54,908
Could be from a dating site.

605
00:46:54,933 --> 00:46:55,859
She's not!

606
00:46:56,775 --> 00:46:59,108
It's because you've been acting awfully fishy lately.

607
00:46:59,182 --> 00:47:00,708
So we're keeping an eye on you.

608
00:47:00,733 --> 00:47:02,539
I don't need a baby sitter, okay?

609
00:47:04,882 --> 00:47:06,150
The switches stopped.

610
00:47:06,865 --> 00:47:09,935
My calls never connected and texts never went through.

611
00:47:10,135 --> 00:47:12,970
That's why I decided to go see Mitsuha in person.

612
00:47:14,689 --> 00:47:16,078
I wanted to see her.

613
00:47:16,728 --> 00:47:17,174
But...

614
00:47:19,472 --> 00:47:20,314
What?

615
00:47:20,562 --> 00:47:22,427
You don't know where she is exactly?

616
00:47:22,620 --> 00:47:24,826
The town's landscape is your only clue?

617
00:47:25,032 --> 00:47:25,811
Yeah.

618
00:47:28,605 --> 00:47:30,562
And you can't contact her?

619
00:47:30,808 --> 00:47:32,042
What's that about?

620
00:47:32,667 --> 00:47:34,963
Where are we? You're a terrible tour guide.

621
00:47:34,988 --> 00:47:36,115
'Cause I'm not one!

622
00:47:36,514 --> 00:47:39,442
Oh, well. Guess we'll help you search.

623
00:47:39,812 --> 00:47:42,392
Ah! It's so cute! Look, Taki!

624
00:47:42,764 --> 00:47:44,079
Seriously, guys?

625
00:47:44,150 --> 00:47:45,928
It moved! Aw!

626
00:48:15,354 --> 00:48:16,448
This is a lost cause.

627
00:48:16,508 --> 00:48:20,323
What? After everything that we've done for you today?

628
00:48:22,951 --> 00:48:24,980
You haven't done anything.

629
00:48:28,820 --> 00:48:30,156
One Takayama ramen.

630
00:48:30,299 --> 00:48:31,519
One Takayama ramen.

631
00:48:31,908 --> 00:48:33,326
I guess I'll have the same.

632
00:48:33,512 --> 00:48:34,264
Sure.

633
00:48:34,822 --> 00:48:36,139
Three orders of ramen.

634
00:48:36,289 --> 00:48:36,819
Got it.

635
00:48:39,115 --> 00:48:41,230
Think we can make it back to Tokyo tonight?

636
00:48:41,255 --> 00:48:43,378
Well, I think we'll be cutting it close.

637
00:48:43,438 --> 00:48:44,238
Let me take a look.

638
00:48:44,455 --> 00:48:45,347
'K, thanks.

639
00:48:45,372 --> 00:48:47,556
Wait, Taki, you sure about that?

640
00:48:49,992 --> 00:48:54,354
Yeah. I kinda feel like maybe I've been
barking up the wrong tree this whole time.

641
00:48:58,962 --> 00:49:01,595
Hey. That's a sketch of Itomori, isn't it?

642
00:49:03,779 --> 00:49:04,918
It's drawn really well.

643
00:49:05,652 --> 00:49:07,158
Come take a look at this, Hun!

644
00:49:08,813 --> 00:49:10,355
Yeah, that's Itomori.

645
00:49:10,906 --> 00:49:12,047
It takes me back.

646
00:49:12,088 --> 00:49:14,398
My husband was born and raised there, you know.

647
00:49:14,765 --> 00:49:15,727
Itomori?

648
00:49:18,023 --> 00:49:20,426
Yes, of course! That's the place!

649
00:49:20,734 --> 00:49:22,148
It's nearby, right?

650
00:49:22,756 --> 00:49:23,712
You don't...

651
00:49:24,130 --> 00:49:25,536
Itomori was...

652
00:49:25,985 --> 00:49:27,313
Itomori?

653
00:49:28,009 --> 00:49:28,435
Wait!

654
00:49:28,460 --> 00:49:28,861
But that's where...

655
00:49:28,886 --> 00:49:30,628
Isn't that the area where that comet...?

656
00:50:20,930 --> 00:50:24,021
Hey, is this place really where she's from?

657
00:50:24,241 --> 00:50:27,680
No way. Taki must've just
confused this with somewhere else.

658
00:50:27,999 --> 00:50:28,949
No, I didn't.

659
00:50:30,085 --> 00:50:31,309
This was the place.

660
00:50:32,163 --> 00:50:34,540
This schoolyard. These mountains.

661
00:50:34,670 --> 00:50:37,422
Even this high school here! I remember it all!

662
00:50:37,605 --> 00:50:39,138
There's no way you could.

663
00:50:39,630 --> 00:50:42,749
You've gotta know about that
disaster three years ago, right?

664
00:50:43,552 --> 00:50:45,312
Hundreds of people died.

665
00:50:45,459 --> 00:50:46,115
They died?

666
00:50:47,890 --> 00:50:49,010
Three years ago?

667
00:50:49,892 --> 00:50:50,886
It can't be.

668
00:50:53,049 --> 00:50:54,056
There's no way.

669
00:50:54,700 --> 00:50:55,594
I mean,

670
00:50:56,279 --> 00:50:58,214
I still have the memos she wrote.

671
00:51:15,938 --> 00:51:17,039
They're fading...

672
00:51:27,727 --> 00:51:31,858
Comet Tia-mat, with an orbital period of 1,200 years,

673
00:51:32,346 --> 00:51:35,301
made a close approach to Earth three years ago in October.

674
00:51:36,529 --> 00:51:39,733
Nobody foresaw that its nucleus
would split at its perigee.

675
00:51:46,658 --> 00:51:50,147
The fragment that broke off of it
became a meteor and struck Japan.

676
00:51:52,485 --> 00:51:55,884
It looks like that day was the
same date as the autumn festival.

677
00:51:56,892 --> 00:51:58,462
The point of impact was here.

678
00:51:59,505 --> 00:52:03,833
At 8:42 p.m. it fell right around where
people were gathered for the festival.

679
00:52:08,872 --> 00:52:10,513
Over 500 died.

680
00:52:11,067 --> 00:52:13,077
It was a third of the town's population,

681
00:52:13,631 --> 00:52:15,796
and now nobody lives in Itomori anymore.

682
00:52:24,905 --> 00:52:26,151
Teshigawara...

683
00:52:26,745 --> 00:52:27,764
and Sayaka.

684
00:52:32,528 --> 00:52:34,097
Huh? That's her?

685
00:52:34,441 --> 00:52:36,355
You were wrong. You gotta be.

686
00:52:36,709 --> 00:52:39,679
After all, this girl here died three years ago!

687
00:52:40,452 --> 00:52:44,670
Just two or three weeks ago she
said that I'd be able to see the comet.

688
00:52:45,604 --> 00:52:46,405
That means...!

689
00:52:47,447 --> 00:52:49,075
You're dreaming right now.

690
00:52:49,746 --> 00:52:50,152
I...

691
00:52:50,211 --> 00:52:50,955
aren't you?

692
00:52:53,156 --> 00:52:53,843
I...

693
00:52:56,359 --> 00:52:57,985
What... was I?

694
00:53:11,818 --> 00:53:13,199
Sounds lively over there.

695
00:53:13,692 --> 00:53:16,579
They only have one room left. I'm really sorry.

696
00:53:16,699 --> 00:53:17,751
It's not a problem.

697
00:53:19,031 --> 00:53:20,126
How's Taki?

698
00:53:20,293 --> 00:53:22,533
He's still reading articles on Itomori.

699
00:53:22,899 --> 00:53:26,706
He's going through all those newspapers
and magazines at random. Seems obsessive.

700
00:53:31,703 --> 00:53:32,752
What is it?

701
00:53:32,969 --> 00:53:34,939
Oh, sorry. You smoke, huh?

702
00:53:35,203 --> 00:53:38,264
Yeah. I did quit at one point.

703
00:53:39,635 --> 00:53:41,979
What do you think about what Taki's been saying?

704
00:53:45,529 --> 00:53:47,399
I had feelings for him, you know.

705
00:53:48,270 --> 00:53:49,815
The way he's been recently.

706
00:53:50,394 --> 00:53:52,384
I mean, he was a nice guy before,

707
00:53:52,544 --> 00:53:54,158
but he's even nicer now.

708
00:53:55,001 --> 00:53:58,425
Kind of... frantic. It was cute.

709
00:53:59,426 --> 00:54:03,378
Although I do think what he's been
telling us is definitely strange sounding.

710
00:54:05,884 --> 00:54:08,807
But in the end, the fact remains that Taki's met someone,

711
00:54:08,913 --> 00:54:10,917
and that someone is the reason he changed.

712
00:54:12,445 --> 00:54:13,948
That much is for sure.

713
00:54:29,700 --> 00:54:31,218
It was all just a dream.

714
00:54:33,186 --> 00:54:34,781
I recognized the landscape

715
00:54:35,119 --> 00:54:38,083
because I unconsciously remembered
the news from three years ago.

716
00:54:40,479 --> 00:54:43,436
If it's not that, is she... a ghost?

717
00:54:43,815 --> 00:54:44,464
Or...

718
00:54:45,495 --> 00:54:48,363
did I just make it up? The whole thing.

719
00:54:52,372 --> 00:54:53,927
What was her name?

720
00:54:54,839 --> 00:54:55,884
I can't remember.

721
00:54:58,629 --> 00:55:01,153
Tsukasa said he was gonna go ahead and take a bath.

722
00:55:01,364 --> 00:55:02,389
Miss Okudera.

723
00:55:03,061 --> 00:55:04,867
Uh... I, um...

724
00:55:05,647 --> 00:55:08,345
I realize I've been saying a lot of strange things.

725
00:55:09,215 --> 00:55:11,038
I'm really sorry, and thank you.

726
00:55:19,858 --> 00:55:22,003
Braided cords. Pretty.

727
00:55:23,156 --> 00:55:24,601
That band on your wrist,

728
00:55:25,088 --> 00:55:26,155
that's one, isn't it?

729
00:55:27,240 --> 00:55:29,291
Oh, this thing? Guess so.

730
00:55:29,759 --> 00:55:32,709
Somebody... Someone gave it to me.

731
00:55:33,572 --> 00:55:36,179
I wear it sometimes as kind of a lucky charm.

732
00:55:38,956 --> 00:55:40,213
Who was it?

733
00:55:42,749 --> 00:55:45,802
It's late. Why don't you go down and take a bath too?

734
00:55:45,950 --> 00:55:47,475
Sure. Wait.

735
00:55:50,875 --> 00:55:53,415
Yeah, someone who makes these.

736
00:55:53,757 --> 00:55:55,424
They once told me something.

737
00:55:55,697 --> 00:55:57,990
The cords represent the flow of time.

738
00:55:58,619 --> 00:56:01,735
They twist and tangle, unravel and connect.

739
00:56:02,220 --> 00:56:04,393
And that's what time is.

740
00:56:06,706 --> 00:56:07,961
Maybe if I could...

741
00:56:34,464 --> 00:56:35,215
Taki.

742
00:56:36,066 --> 00:56:36,936
Taki.

743
00:56:38,020 --> 00:56:39,216
Taki!

744
00:56:41,173 --> 00:56:42,522
Don't you remember?

745
00:57:05,560 --> 00:57:06,554
Taki...

746
00:57:30,878 --> 00:57:32,836
Eat this bento up there.

747
00:57:33,983 --> 00:57:35,725
Your drawing of Itomori,

748
00:57:36,681 --> 00:57:37,958
you did a real good job.

749
00:58:15,679 --> 00:58:17,572
They assemble and take shape.

750
00:58:18,227 --> 00:58:19,634
They twist, tangle,

751
00:58:20,050 --> 00:58:23,446
unravel now and then, break and reconnect.

752
00:58:24,837 --> 00:58:26,385
That's what a union is.

753
00:58:27,216 --> 00:58:28,800
What time is.

754
00:58:40,189 --> 00:58:41,288
There it is!

755
00:58:43,748 --> 00:58:44,890
It's really there.

756
00:58:46,259 --> 00:58:48,360
It wasn't a dream.

757
00:59:19,620 --> 00:59:22,804
What lies ahead... is the netherworld.

758
00:59:45,603 --> 00:59:46,937
It's still here.

759
00:59:49,079 --> 00:59:50,902
This was Yotsuha's,

760
00:59:51,746 --> 00:59:53,013
and this was mine.

761
00:59:55,797 --> 00:59:57,276
This was before the comet.

762
00:59:58,007 --> 01:00:00,067
So when I switched places with her,

763
01:00:00,663 --> 01:00:02,643
it was also three years in the past.

764
01:00:04,558 --> 01:00:07,498
Our times got tangled somehow.

765
01:00:09,170 --> 01:00:10,877
This is half of her.

766
01:00:26,112 --> 01:00:26,853
Musubi.

767
01:00:28,534 --> 01:00:31,099
If it's true, and time can be unraveled,

768
01:00:32,183 --> 01:00:34,054
just give me one chance.

769
01:00:49,011 --> 01:00:50,033
A comet!

770
01:01:55,293 --> 01:01:57,939
Your name's going to be Mitsuha.

771
01:02:04,746 --> 01:02:06,962
Both of you are my treasures.

772
01:02:07,220 --> 01:02:09,456
You're going to be a big sister.

773
01:02:12,130 --> 01:02:14,652
I'm so sorry, me dears.

774
01:02:16,692 --> 01:02:19,760
Dad, when is Mommy coming home?

775
01:02:20,909 --> 01:02:22,444
I couldn't help her.

776
01:02:22,469 --> 01:02:24,150
Get a hold of yourself!

777
01:02:24,234 --> 01:02:25,879
Who cares about the shrine?!

778
01:02:25,904 --> 01:02:27,512
But you're in charge now!

779
01:02:27,537 --> 01:02:29,939
I loved Futaba! Not Miyamizu Shrine.

780
01:02:29,964 --> 01:02:30,992
Get out!

781
01:02:34,653 --> 01:02:37,818
Now listen to me, girls, starting today,

782
01:02:38,172 --> 01:02:40,247
you'll be living with Grandma.

783
01:02:44,811 --> 01:02:46,490
Who am I?

784
01:02:46,641 --> 01:02:47,665
Who are you?

785
01:02:47,951 --> 01:02:49,466
Don't be full of yourself!

786
01:02:49,481 --> 01:02:51,362
Like you have a girlfriend.

787
01:02:51,501 --> 01:02:52,600
Must be nice.

788
01:02:52,911 --> 01:02:55,076
They've probably met up about now.

789
01:02:56,511 --> 01:02:57,600
Why am I...?

790
01:02:57,731 --> 01:02:59,075
I'm going to Tokyo.

791
01:02:59,111 --> 01:03:01,095
What? Wait, Sis!

792
01:03:03,617 --> 01:03:04,370
Grandma.

793
01:03:05,193 --> 01:03:06,951
would you mind doing me a favor?

794
01:03:08,083 --> 01:03:09,678
Oh, yeah, the comet.

795
01:03:11,131 --> 01:03:13,514
It'll be at its brightest today, right?

796
01:03:14,241 --> 01:03:16,334
Mitsuha! Don't go there!

797
01:03:17,381 --> 01:03:21,431
Mitsuha, You've gotta get out
of town before the comet strikes!

798
01:03:24,185 --> 01:03:25,923
Mitsuha, run!

799
01:03:26,791 --> 01:03:29,584
Mitsuha. Mitsuha!

800
01:03:29,746 --> 01:03:32,394
Mitsuha!

801
01:03:49,947 --> 01:03:52,451
Mitsuha. She's alive.

802
01:04:03,513 --> 01:04:05,592
Let me guess, you're touching your boo...

803
01:04:08,483 --> 01:04:09,911
Her sister!

804
01:04:12,237 --> 01:04:14,815
Yotsuha!

805
01:04:17,735 --> 01:04:20,030
I think she's finally lost it.

806
01:04:20,197 --> 01:04:23,356
Just for today, I'm gonna head out first.

807
01:04:23,603 --> 01:04:24,639
She's lost it.

808
01:04:24,989 --> 01:04:28,722
Really lost it. Totally, totally lost it.

809
01:04:28,747 --> 01:04:34,162
For all you star-gazers out there, the comet Tia-mat
has been visible to the naked eye for about a week now.

810
01:04:34,460 --> 01:04:38,055
Tonight it will finally reach its perigee around 7:40 p.m.

811
01:04:38,250 --> 01:04:40,297
and be at its maximum brightness
when viewed from the Earth's surface.

812
01:04:40,752 --> 01:04:43,211
It's tonight. There's still time left.

813
01:04:44,174 --> 01:04:45,768
Morning, Mitsuha.

814
01:04:46,221 --> 01:04:47,320
What's this?

815
01:04:48,542 --> 01:04:51,983
Hold on. You're not Mitsuha, are you?

816
01:04:52,058 --> 01:04:53,298
Wait, how did you...?

817
01:04:54,098 --> 01:04:55,639
You already knew?

818
01:04:56,151 --> 01:05:01,992
No, but watching the way you've been
behaving lately stirred some memories up.

819
01:05:03,564 --> 01:05:05,342
When I was a young girl,

820
01:05:05,897 --> 01:05:08,515
I had some pretty strange dreams myself.

821
01:05:09,843 --> 01:05:11,133
Though it's been so long,

822
01:05:11,163 --> 01:05:15,817
the memories of who I became in those
dreams have pretty much faded at this point.

823
01:05:16,682 --> 01:05:17,621
Faded.

824
01:05:17,997 --> 01:05:19,698
Treasure the experience.

825
01:05:19,805 --> 01:05:22,345
Dreams eventually will fade away.

826
01:05:23,203 --> 01:05:25,708
I went through similar times myself,

827
01:05:26,025 --> 01:05:27,703
and so did your mother.

828
01:05:29,219 --> 01:05:32,552
What if... all those dreams
that the Miyamizu people had...

829
01:05:32,905 --> 01:05:34,426
...it had to do with today?

830
01:05:35,876 --> 01:05:37,976
Grandma, you have to listen to me!

831
01:05:38,973 --> 01:05:42,615
Tonight, the comet is going to fall on Itomori.

832
01:05:42,737 --> 01:05:44,085
You're all gonna die!

833
01:05:51,324 --> 01:05:52,829
"Nobody's gonna believe that"?

834
01:05:53,236 --> 01:05:55,679
I didn't expect that out of Mitsuha's grandma.

835
01:05:56,213 --> 01:05:57,310
It doesn't matter!

836
01:05:57,377 --> 01:05:59,549
There's no way I'm gonna let them all die!

837
01:06:00,751 --> 01:06:03,788
Mitshua! What happened to...?

838
01:06:05,034 --> 01:06:07,447
What'd you...? Your hair!

839
01:06:07,516 --> 01:06:10,210
Ah, the haircut? Looked better before, huh?

840
01:06:10,235 --> 01:06:11,979
No! I-It's good!

841
01:06:12,004 --> 01:06:15,714
Never mind that! If we don't do
something about tonight, we'll all die!

842
01:06:15,797 --> 01:06:16,355
What?

843
01:06:18,346 --> 01:06:20,385
It's up to us to save everyone!

844
01:06:25,231 --> 01:06:27,122
Wait! Shouldn't you be in school?

845
01:06:27,392 --> 01:06:31,611
Well, we sort of have to save the town, or something.

846
01:06:33,795 --> 01:06:34,840
The warning system?

847
01:06:34,923 --> 01:06:36,699
Yeah, those speakers all over town.

848
01:06:41,981 --> 01:06:43,930
I get it. It could work!

849
01:06:44,264 --> 01:06:45,782
Nice job, Teshi!

850
01:06:45,918 --> 01:06:48,514
Hey, I don't think you should be sitting so close to me.

851
01:06:48,539 --> 01:06:50,887
What's wrong? Uh-oh! You shy?

852
01:06:50,911 --> 01:06:53,779
Would ya quit it? It ain't proper! And you know it!

853
01:06:57,774 --> 01:06:59,044
Such a gentleman!

854
01:07:02,098 --> 01:07:04,516
I bought all the snacks, guys! Here's the change.

855
01:07:04,541 --> 01:07:05,878
Sorry for the trouble.

856
01:07:05,903 --> 01:07:07,375
