city hospital for an examination.

897
01:09:12,157 --> 01:09:15,395
We will continue this discussion
after you've seen a doctor.

898
01:09:17,571 --> 01:09:18,422
You!

899
01:09:20,300 --> 01:09:21,535
You son of a...

900
01:09:30,180 --> 01:09:31,042
Mitsuha?

901
01:09:32,677 --> 01:09:33,459
No...

902
01:09:34,570 --> 01:09:35,664
Wait a minute...

903
01:09:37,360 --> 01:09:38,231
Who are you?

904
01:09:53,698 --> 01:09:55,029
I'll see you guys at the festival.

905
01:09:55,089 --> 01:09:57,516
We'll meet you at the steps to
the shrine! Don't be late, okay?

906
01:09:57,541 --> 01:09:58,324
Bye-bye!

907
01:09:58,395 --> 01:09:58,957
See ya.

908
01:09:58,997 --> 01:09:59,777
Later.

909
01:10:01,652 --> 01:10:02,772
You shouldn't go!

910
01:10:03,402 --> 01:10:05,955
You've gotta leave town! Tell all of your friends!

911
01:10:05,981 --> 01:10:07,407
What's wrong with ya?

912
01:10:07,563 --> 01:10:08,468
Mitsuha!

913
01:10:08,493 --> 01:10:09,387
What was that about?

914
01:10:09,411 --> 01:10:10,629
Come on. Let's go.

915
01:10:10,977 --> 01:10:13,016
What're you doing, huh?

916
01:10:13,704 --> 01:10:15,017
If it was Mitsuha,

917
01:10:15,659 --> 01:10:17,692
would she have been able to convince him?

918
01:10:17,997 --> 01:10:19,223
Is all this my fault?

919
01:10:19,838 --> 01:10:23,415
Yotsuha! Promise me that you'll
leave town with Grandma before dark!

920
01:10:23,681 --> 01:10:24,206
What?

921
01:10:24,311 --> 01:10:25,965
You're gonna die if you stay here!

922
01:10:26,011 --> 01:10:27,274
What're you talking about?

923
01:10:27,366 --> 01:10:29,876
And why'd you suddenly go to Tokyo yesterday?

924
01:10:29,908 --> 01:10:32,369
You've been acting really strange lately!

925
01:10:33,971 --> 01:10:35,298
Went to Tokyo?

926
01:10:35,426 --> 01:10:37,861
Hey, Mitsuha!

927
01:10:40,331 --> 01:10:41,704
How'd it go with your old man?

928
01:10:44,444 --> 01:10:46,127
Hey! Mitsuha!

929
01:10:46,881 --> 01:10:48,260
What's with your sister?

930
01:10:48,528 --> 01:10:49,577
Dunno.

931
01:10:59,760 --> 01:11:01,408
Could she be over there?

932
01:11:02,074 --> 01:11:04,202
What's that? What's over there?

933
01:11:04,911 --> 01:11:06,466
Let me use your bike, Teshi.

934
01:11:06,497 --> 01:11:08,876
Hey! Mitsuha!

935
01:11:09,974 --> 01:11:11,240
And what do we do?

936
01:11:11,658 --> 01:11:13,411
Get things ready like we planned!

937
01:11:13,858 --> 01:11:15,206
I'm counting on you!

938
01:11:41,946 --> 01:11:43,970
Oh my gosh! I'm Taki again.

939
01:11:47,057 --> 01:11:49,502
But what was Taki doing out here?

940
01:11:59,294 --> 01:12:00,214
The town...

941
01:12:00,933 --> 01:12:02,434
It's gone.

942
01:12:12,286 --> 01:12:15,148
So does that mean...

943
01:12:17,892 --> 01:12:19,347
...they died?

944
01:12:30,374 --> 01:12:31,261
Taki.

945
01:12:32,107 --> 01:12:33,007
Taki!

946
01:12:35,614 --> 01:12:37,054
Don't you remember?

947
01:12:50,005 --> 01:12:51,885
I'm going to Tokyo for a few hours.

948
01:12:52,106 --> 01:12:53,479
What? Right now?

949
01:12:53,898 --> 01:12:54,794
But why?

950
01:12:55,257 --> 01:12:56,049
For a date.

951
01:12:56,697 --> 01:12:58,647
You have a boyfriend in Tokyo?

952
01:12:58,672 --> 01:13:00,781
I didn't say it was a date for me.

953
01:13:02,001 --> 01:13:03,561
I'll be back tonight.

954
01:13:06,937 --> 01:13:08,324
If I suddenly show up,

955
01:13:08,471 --> 01:13:11,741
will it be a nuisance? Or a surprise?

956
01:13:12,478 --> 01:13:14,302
He might not like it if I do.

957
01:13:22,414 --> 01:13:26,424
The number you are trying to reach is
currently outside the cellular network.

958
01:13:26,794 --> 01:13:28,365
I guess it won't happen.

959
01:13:29,107 --> 01:13:31,175
But what if it did?

960
01:13:32,048 --> 01:13:35,116
What would I do? Would I annoy him?

961
01:13:36,029 --> 01:13:37,351
Would it be awkward?

962
01:13:38,014 --> 01:13:41,945
Or maybe... he'd be glad to see me.

963
01:13:43,740 --> 01:13:47,397
The number you are trying to reach is
currently outside the cellular network.

964
01:13:48,774 --> 01:13:50,421
I guess we won't meet.

965
01:13:52,443 --> 01:13:52,974
But...

966
01:13:54,137 --> 01:13:56,457
...there's one thing I'm certain of.

967
01:13:57,844 --> 01:13:59,280
If we see each other,

968
01:13:59,827 --> 01:14:02,110
we'll definitely know right away.

969
01:14:03,239 --> 01:14:05,751
That you were the one who was in me.

970
01:14:07,017 --> 01:14:10,874
And that I was the one who was in you.

971
01:14:10,899 --> 01:14:11,538
Sorry.

972
01:14:14,842 --> 01:14:18,676
The train will be arriving
momentarily. Please stand behind the line.

973
01:14:19,204 --> 01:14:22,224
When entering the train, please mind the gap.

974
01:14:43,194 --> 01:14:44,191
Excuse me.

975
01:14:44,391 --> 01:14:46,830
The doors are now closing.

976
01:15:16,807 --> 01:15:20,979
That time three years ago, before I even knew you...

977
01:15:21,015 --> 01:15:24,188
Yotsuya. The platform will be on the right.

978
01:15:24,849 --> 01:15:25,776
Taki.

979
01:15:27,127 --> 01:15:28,091
Taki.

980
01:15:30,120 --> 01:15:31,078
Taki.

981
01:15:32,513 --> 01:15:34,341
Um, it's me!

982
01:15:37,049 --> 01:15:39,170
Don't you remember?

983
01:15:40,505 --> 01:15:41,997
Sorry, who are you?

984
01:15:46,838 --> 01:15:48,001
I-I'm sorry.

985
01:15:56,014 --> 01:15:57,308
But he's Taki.

986
01:15:59,083 --> 01:16:00,329
What a weird girl.

987
01:16:00,527 --> 01:16:04,604
Yotsuya. Yotsuya. Stand clear of the doors.

988
01:16:09,371 --> 01:16:10,114
Hold on!

989
01:16:10,943 --> 01:16:12,577
But what's your name?

990
01:16:13,838 --> 01:16:14,739
Mitsuha!

991
01:16:15,159 --> 01:16:17,761
My name is... Mitsuha!

992
01:16:24,342 --> 01:16:27,442
Three years ago, you showed up.

993
01:16:28,543 --> 01:16:31,302
It was... to see me!

994
01:16:42,872 --> 01:16:43,636
Taki?

995
01:16:53,122 --> 01:16:54,479
Mitsuha!

996
01:16:55,598 --> 01:16:56,350
Taki!?

997
01:17:11,519 --> 01:17:12,892
Mitsuha!

998
01:17:13,564 --> 01:17:17,221
You're here, right? Inside my body!

999
01:17:17,735 --> 01:17:18,646
Taki!

1000
01:17:20,044 --> 01:17:21,242
Taki, where are you?

1001
01:17:22,330 --> 01:17:23,338
That was Mitsuha.

1002
01:17:24,467 --> 01:17:26,230
I can hear her voice, but...

1003
01:17:27,289 --> 01:17:29,717
Taki, where are you?

1004
01:17:30,511 --> 01:17:31,531
Taki!

1005
01:17:44,948 --> 01:17:47,188
Taki, are you...?

1006
01:17:47,854 --> 01:17:49,364
Are you there?

1007
01:18:15,031 --> 01:18:15,959
Magic hour.

1008
01:18:31,108 --> 01:18:31,886
Mitsuha.

1009
01:18:38,828 --> 01:18:39,521
Taki.

1010
01:18:41,018 --> 01:18:41,820
Taki!

1011
01:18:42,749 --> 01:18:44,069
You're really here.

1012
01:18:48,819 --> 01:18:49,967
Taki!

1013
01:18:49,992 --> 01:18:51,663
I came all this way to see you.

1014
01:18:52,396 --> 01:18:53,761
Which wasn't easy,

1015
01:18:53,988 --> 01:18:56,130
since you were pretty far away.

1016
01:18:57,370 --> 01:18:59,009
Huh? How is that even...?

1017
01:18:59,600 --> 01:19:01,217
Because back then...

1018
01:19:01,443 --> 01:19:03,803
Well, I drank some of your <i>kuchikamizake</i>.

1019
01:19:08,080 --> 01:19:09,877
You... You drank that?

1020
01:19:11,081 --> 01:19:12,598
Stupid pervert!

1021
01:19:12,623 --> 01:19:13,239
Wh-What?

1022
01:19:13,455 --> 01:19:14,465
Yeah! That's right!

1023
01:19:14,490 --> 01:19:16,938
You were touching my boobies, weren't you?

1024
01:19:17,230 --> 01:19:18,715
Wh...?! H-How do you even...?

1025
01:19:18,740 --> 01:19:20,108
'Cause Yotsuha saw you!

1026
01:19:20,133 --> 01:19:24,125
I-I just... I couldn't help
myself! But it was just one time.

1027
01:19:24,150 --> 01:19:25,497
Just the one time?

1028
01:19:27,459 --> 01:19:29,872
How many times isn't the issue!

1029
01:19:30,396 --> 01:19:31,346
Sorry.

1030
01:19:31,800 --> 01:19:33,827
Wait, is that...?

1031
01:19:34,617 --> 01:19:38,241
Oh, yeah, it's yours, but you visited before I knew you.

1032
01:19:38,742 --> 01:19:40,277
So I didn't know who you were.

1033
01:19:41,455 --> 01:19:42,228
Here.

1034
01:19:43,039 --> 01:19:44,818
I kept it for three years.

1035
01:19:45,440 --> 01:19:47,210
But I think it's time you got it back.

1036
01:19:57,896 --> 01:19:58,856
What do ya think?

1037
01:19:58,979 --> 01:20:01,761
Oh, uh, well... It's not bad.

1038
01:20:01,940 --> 01:20:03,454
Oh, you're lying!

1039
01:20:05,121 --> 01:20:05,814
Busted.

1040
01:20:05,911 --> 01:20:07,640
Why you gotta be like that?

1041
01:20:22,477 --> 01:20:26,781
Hey, Mitsuha, you still have a lot to do. Listen.

1042
01:20:27,730 --> 01:20:28,740
It's coming.

1043
01:20:29,209 --> 01:20:31,816
Don't worry. You still have enough time.

1044
01:20:32,790 --> 01:20:33,891
I'll do my best.

1045
01:20:35,586 --> 01:20:38,162
It looks like magic hour's almost...

1046
01:20:38,509 --> 01:20:39,191
...over.

1047
01:20:41,850 --> 01:20:42,864
Hey, Mitsuha.

1048
01:20:43,265 --> 01:20:45,521
Just so we don't forget things when we wake up.

1049
01:20:50,302 --> 01:20:51,911
Let's write down our names.

1050
01:20:52,983 --> 01:20:53,523
Here.

1051
01:21:05,960 --> 01:21:06,758
Mitsuha?

1052
01:21:09,709 --> 01:21:11,849
Hey, Mitsuha?

1053
01:21:20,594 --> 01:21:22,138
I was planning to tell you...

1054
01:21:23,823 --> 01:21:25,638
...that wherever you are in the world,

1055
01:21:25,917 --> 01:21:28,642
I swear that I'll find you again, no matter what.

1056
01:21:32,410 --> 01:21:34,513
Your name... is Mitsuha.

1057
01:21:36,180 --> 01:21:38,230
It'll be okay. I'll remember.

1058
01:21:38,826 --> 01:21:42,863
Mitsuha, Mitsuha, Mitsuha! Your name's Mitsuha!

1059
01:21:43,056 --> 01:21:44,225
Your name is...

1060
01:21:55,492 --> 01:21:56,181
Who

1061
01:21:57,002 --> 01:21:57,913
are you?

1062
01:22:00,067 --> 01:22:02,997
And what did I even come here for?

1063
01:22:03,856 --> 01:22:06,760
I came... I came all this way to see her!

1064
01:22:07,146 --> 01:22:08,743
I came to save her.

1065
01:22:08,933 --> 01:22:10,646
I wanted her to be alive.

1066
01:22:11,022 --> 01:22:12,404
Who was it again?

1067
01:22:12,600 --> 01:22:13,377
Who?

1068
01:22:13,566 --> 01:22:15,130
Who did I come to see?

1069
01:22:15,568 --> 01:22:16,925
Someone precious.

1070
01:22:17,034 --> 01:22:18,845
Someone that I don't wanna forget.

1071
01:22:19,457 --> 01:22:20,788
Someone I shouldn't!

1072
01:22:21,740 --> 01:22:22,601
Who was it?

1073
01:22:22,990 --> 01:22:24,212
Who was it?

1074
01:22:24,649 --> 01:22:26,647
Who? Who?

1075
01:22:26,871 --> 01:22:28,153
What's your name?!

1076
01:22:43,430 --> 01:22:46,734
Taki. Taki. Taki!

1077
01:22:47,167 --> 01:22:50,790
It'll be fine. I'll remember. I'll never forget!

1078
01:22:51,324 --> 01:22:53,296
Taki. Taki!

1079
01:22:53,751 --> 01:22:56,516
Your name is Taki!

1080
01:23:11,263 --> 01:23:12,208
Teshi!

1081
01:23:12,703 --> 01:23:13,581
Mitsuha!

1082
01:23:14,210 --> 01:23:15,591
Where the heck have you been?

1083
01:23:15,616 --> 01:23:17,436
He said sorry for breaking your bike.

1084
01:23:17,611 --> 01:23:19,368
Wha...? Who did?

1085
01:23:19,393 --> 01:23:20,134
I did!

1086
01:23:21,470 --> 01:23:23,464
You're gonna have to explain it to me later.

1087
01:23:28,267 --> 01:23:30,884
That thing is going to fall, right? For real?

1088
01:23:31,107 --> 01:23:33,332
For real. I saw it with my own eyes!

1089
01:23:33,466 --> 01:23:35,379
What? You did, huh?

1090
01:23:35,909 --> 01:23:37,965
Well, I guess it's settled then.

1091
01:23:39,227 --> 01:23:41,115
We're both officially criminals.

1092
01:23:42,816 --> 01:23:46,129
What? Do I really have to?

1093
01:23:46,162 --> 01:23:47,859
Once the town's power goes out,

1094
01:23:47,884 --> 01:23:50,070
the emergency generators should kick in right away.

1095
01:23:50,163 --> 01:23:52,267
Use the broadcast equipment once it does.

1096
01:23:52,446 --> 01:23:53,741
Don't be scared, Saya.

1097
01:23:53,793 --> 01:23:55,942
And repeat it as many times as you can.

1098
01:23:56,990 --> 01:23:58,435
You can do it!

1099
01:23:58,633 --> 01:24:01,656
Aw, nuts. It's do or die!

1100
01:24:07,924 --> 01:24:09,425
Shouldn't it be going off?

1101
01:24:09,440 --> 01:24:10,557
Hell if I know!

1102
01:24:21,860 --> 01:24:22,632
What was that?

1103
01:24:22,657 --> 01:24:24,625
That was pretty loud too. Look over there!

1104
01:24:50,150 --> 01:24:51,746
Hey, look! Up there!

1105
01:25:01,520 --> 01:25:04,361
This is Itomori Town Hall.

1106
01:25:04,780 --> 01:25:08,413
Reports of an explosion at the substation are coming in.

1107
01:25:08,438 --> 01:25:09,860
Did I just hear that right?

1108
01:25:09,885 --> 01:25:13,627
Wildfires are possible, as well
as the threat of more explosions.

1109
01:25:14,364 --> 01:25:16,557
Residents in the following areas,

1110
01:25:16,752 --> 01:25:20,312
please evacuate to Itomori High School immediately.

1111
01:25:21,110 --> 01:25:22,872
Kadoiri District

1112
01:25:23,477 --> 01:25:24,973
Sakagami District...

1113
01:25:25,100 --> 01:25:26,100
Honey, we should go.

1114
01:25:26,125 --> 01:25:27,917
The broadcast isn't coming from us?

1115
01:25:27,987 --> 01:25:29,269
Well, who the hell is it then?

1116
01:25:29,294 --> 01:25:31,254
Miyamori District.

1117
01:25:32,129 --> 01:25:33,809
Oyazawa District.

1118
01:25:34,736 --> 01:25:36,221
Let's go, Mitsuha!

1119
01:25:38,333 --> 01:25:39,329
Teshi!

1120
01:25:45,910 --> 01:25:49,385
Everyone, run! There's a wildfire!

1121
01:25:49,410 --> 01:25:51,422
Wildfire! Please run!

1122
01:25:51,447 --> 01:25:53,032
Get outta here! Run!

1123
01:25:53,057 --> 01:25:55,833
It's not safe here! Please evacuate!

1124
01:25:56,324 --> 01:25:59,679
It's not working. We're running outta time! Mitsuha!

1125
01:26:01,305 --> 01:26:02,147
What's wrong?

1126
01:26:03,280 --> 01:26:04,548
What is it?

1127
01:26:05,196 --> 01:26:07,768
I can't remember what his name is anymore!

1128
01:26:09,950 --> 01:26:11,358
What is with you?!

1129
01:26:11,434 --> 01:26:13,455
You're the one who started all of this!

1130
01:26:14,042 --> 01:26:16,675
We can't evacuate everyone without firefighters!

1131
01:26:17,369 --> 01:26:19,595
Get going! You gotta convince your old man!

1132
01:26:21,523 --> 01:26:24,042
This is Itomori Town Hall.

1133
01:26:25,749 --> 01:26:28,006
Reports of an explosion at the substation are coming in.

1134
01:26:28,030 --> 01:26:31,128
Everybody! Get to the high school! Hurry!

1135
01:26:33,890 --> 01:26:35,564
Oh, it's Mitsuha.

1136
01:26:38,455 --> 01:26:40,573
Why would terrorists attack way out here?

1137
01:26:40,598 --> 01:26:41,903
What is Chubu Electric saying?

1138
01:26:41,928 --> 01:26:42,978
They're still checking.

1139
01:26:43,362 --> 01:26:45,659
Any update? No wildfires yet?

1140
01:26:45,852 --> 01:26:47,274
You're sure? Got it.

1141
01:26:49,166 --> 01:26:51,439
Make them stop this broadcast immediately!

1142
01:26:51,464 --> 01:26:53,239
Haven't you located its source yet?!

1143
01:26:53,289 --> 01:26:56,027
Mayor! The Takayama sensor station just called!

1144
01:26:56,910 --> 01:26:58,399
From the high school?

1145
01:26:58,817 --> 01:27:02,041
Once again, residents in the following areas,

1146
01:27:02,103 --> 01:27:04,999
please evacuate to Itomori High... Ah!

1147
01:27:05,024 --> 01:27:06,946
What're you doing? Turn that off!

1148
01:27:09,848 --> 01:27:10,901
They got Saya!

1149
01:27:11,031 --> 01:27:11,839
Oh, no!

1150
01:27:15,549 --> 01:27:18,173
What were you thinking, Natori? I swear.

1151
01:27:21,880 --> 01:27:24,295
This is Itomori Town Hall.

1152
01:27:25,377 --> 01:27:28,832
We are currently confirming the reports of the accident.

1153
01:27:29,935 --> 01:27:34,855
We instruct all residents to remain calm
and stay where they are till further notice.

1154
01:27:34,879 --> 01:27:36,292
I guess we have to stay put.

1155
01:27:36,749 --> 01:27:37,640
What is going on?

1156
01:27:37,692 --> 01:27:39,152
So stay on standby.

1157
01:27:39,938 --> 01:27:42,710
Come on, they said everyone should evacuate!

1158
01:27:42,882 --> 01:27:45,070
The high school's the evacuation center!

1159
01:27:45,095 --> 01:27:46,072
Katsuhiko!

1160
01:27:49,436 --> 01:27:52,022
Tell me. What do you think you're doing?

1161
01:27:55,282 --> 01:27:56,460
Sorry, Mitsuha.

1162
01:27:58,049 --> 01:27:59,272
This is the end.

1163
01:28:01,936 --> 01:28:04,897
Oh my god. It's actually splitting apart.

1164
01:28:12,252 --> 01:28:18,031
Look at that! The comet has split into two
large parts, and meteors are now falling to earth!

1165
01:28:18,622 --> 01:28:20,780
I don't believe anyone could've predicted this.

1166
01:28:20,805 --> 01:28:23,017
Either way, we have quite the mystical view here.

1167
01:28:23,039 --> 01:28:26,149
So what does the comet's nucleus splitting mean for us?

1168
01:28:26,599 --> 01:28:28,163
The comet's not within the Roche limit,

1169
01:28:28,192 --> 01:28:31,957
so the nucleus itself must've had a
structural weakness for this to happen.

1170
01:28:32,259 --> 01:28:37,304
Comet Shoemaker-Levy 9 broke apart
and collided with Jupiter in 1994.

1171
01:28:37,688 --> 01:28:38,682
There were at least 21 fragments then.

1172
01:28:38,707 --> 01:28:39,944
I'm going outside to take a look.

1173
01:28:39,969 --> 01:28:41,225
The fragments will likely burn up

1174
01:28:41,239 --> 01:28:44,672
well before reaching the ground, The
probability of a meteor actually landing...

1175
01:28:44,697 --> 01:28:49,109
Scientists were already intently examining
the comet, but never foresaw this development.

1176
01:28:49,188 --> 01:28:50,773
To predict the trajectory...

1177
01:28:50,798 --> 01:28:52,791
As we stand here witnessing this spectacle,

1178
01:28:53,297 --> 01:28:55,984
unassisted and with our bare eyes,

1179
01:28:56,131 --> 01:29:00,299
it strikes me that living in such an
age has never felt more fortunate than now.

1180
01:29:04,273 --> 01:29:07,847
Hey. Who are you?

1181
01:29:11,362 --> 01:29:13,867
Who? Who?

1182
01:29:14,796 --> 01:29:16,059
Who is he?

1183
01:29:16,245 --> 01:29:18,155
Someone precious.

1184
01:29:18,545 --> 01:29:20,036
Someone I shouldn't forget.

1185
01:29:20,562 --> 01:29:22,386
Someone I didn't want to!

1186
01:29:23,268 --> 01:29:27,288
Who? Who? Who are you?

1187
01:29:27,929 --> 01:29:29,380
What's your name?

1188
01:29:35,499 --> 01:29:36,327
Oh, no.

1189
01:29:56,248 --> 01:29:58,309
So that we don't forget things when we wake up,

1190
01:29:58,965 --> 01:30:00,249
let's write down our names.

1191
01:30:09,529 --> 01:30:13,374
"I LOVE YOU"

1192
01:30:28,065 --> 01:30:32,930
Writing this... doesn't help. I won't know your name.

1193
01:30:46,492 --> 01:30:47,457
Dad!

1194
01:30:49,338 --> 01:30:50,031
Mitsuha?

1195
01:30:50,056 --> 01:30:51,081
There you are!

1196
01:30:51,366 --> 01:30:52,827
Don't tell me you're back.

1197
01:30:57,325 --> 01:31:00,027
It was almost like seeing something out of a dream.

1198
01:31:00,915 --> 01:31:04,352
Nothing more or less than a breathtaking view.

1199
01:32:38,658 --> 01:32:39,831
Why am I here?

1200
01:32:41,589 --> 01:32:42,831
What am I doing?

1201
01:32:52,502 --> 01:32:55,616
Next is Yoyogi. Yoyogi.

1202
01:33:08,670 --> 01:33:11,843
The doors are closing. Please be careful.

1203
01:33:14,937 --> 01:33:17,104
I'm always searching for something.

1204
01:33:17,698 --> 01:33:22,393
This feeling has consumed me for some time.

1205
01:33:24,585 --> 01:33:26,545
The reason I applied for this position...

1206
01:33:26,648 --> 01:33:29,944
The landscapes people live in...
To build a city's landscape...

1207
01:33:30,099 --> 01:33:32,850
Even Tokyo, it might vanish too one day.

1208
01:33:33,071 --> 01:33:35,690
And so, I wanna make landscapes that

1209
01:33:35,975 --> 01:33:37,257
how should I put this?

1210
01:33:37,445 --> 01:33:40,896
That can continue to warm people's hearts.

1211
01:33:42,512 --> 01:33:44,799
That bad? How many does that make it?

1212
01:33:44,902 --> 01:33:46,238
I've stopped counting.

1213
01:33:46,252 --> 01:33:47,737
Doesn't sound too promising.

1214
01:33:47,752 --> 01:33:48,621
Who asked you?

1215
01:33:48,646 --> 01:33:50,314
That suit could be the problem.

1216
01:33:50,332 --> 01:33:51,883
It looks just like yours!

1217
01:33:52,011 --> 01:33:53,387
Well, I have two offers.

1218
01:33:53,412 --> 01:33:54,838
I have eight myself.

1219
01:34:00,491 --> 01:34:05,081
Is what I'm searching for... someone? Or somewhere?

1220
01:34:06,291 --> 01:34:08,883
Or am I just searching for the right job?

1221
01:34:09,615 --> 01:34:11,020
I don't even really know.

1222
01:34:12,296 --> 01:34:14,876
Oh, You're job hunting, huh?

1223
01:34:14,901 --> 01:34:16,573
I haven't had much luck though.

1224
01:34:17,386 --> 01:34:19,602
Hey, maybe it's the suit that's killing your chances.

1225
01:34:19,627 --> 01:34:21,345
Does it really look that bad on me?

1226
01:34:26,503 --> 01:34:28,543
So why the sudden call today?

1227
01:34:29,049 --> 01:34:33,529
I was in the area for work and I figured
it had been a while since I saw your face.

1228
01:34:36,319 --> 01:34:39,836
Remember that one time when
we went all the way to Itomori?

1229
01:34:40,288 --> 01:34:43,375
You were still in high school back then, so it was...

1230
01:34:44,262 --> 01:34:45,358
Five years ago.

1231
01:34:45,383 --> 01:34:46,292
That long?

1232
01:34:47,396 --> 01:34:50,204
It seems like... I've forgotten a lot.

1233
01:34:51,603 --> 01:34:53,648
I don't remember all that much either,

1234
01:34:54,090 --> 01:34:55,130
about back then.

1235
01:34:56,225 --> 01:34:57,637
Maybe we argued.

1236
01:34:58,352 --> 01:35:00,928
She and Tsukasa went back to Tokyo without me.

1237
01:35:02,324 --> 01:35:04,637
I spent the night alone on some mountain.

1238
01:35:05,818 --> 01:35:07,283
That's about all I remember.

1239
01:35:10,501 --> 01:35:12,448
But at one point in time,

1240
01:35:12,884 --> 01:35:16,781
I found myself strangely drawn to
the incident involving that comet.

1241
01:35:19,705 --> 01:35:22,894
A fragment of the comet destroyed a town in that disaster.

1242
01:35:23,670 --> 01:35:27,547
But miraculously, most of the
people living in the town were unhurt.

1243
01:35:28,860 --> 01:35:31,649
The town happened to be holding
an emergency drill that day,

1244
01:35:32,191 --> 01:35:34,884
and most of its residents were outside the impact zone.

1245
01:35:36,753 --> 01:35:41,105
The sheer luck and coincidence of it
all sparked various conspiracy theories.

1246
01:35:42,542 --> 01:35:44,519
I read a lot of articles about it back then.

1247
01:35:45,332 --> 01:35:46,465
I was kind of obsessed.

1248
01:35:47,806 --> 01:35:50,504
But whatever the reason I had for my interest,

1249
01:35:50,809 --> 01:35:52,219
is a mystery to me now.

1250
01:35:54,478 --> 01:35:56,448
I didn't even know anybody in that town.

1251
01:36:00,491 --> 01:36:02,958
Thanks for today. This is far enough.

1252
01:36:04,361 --> 01:36:09,777
I do hope that at some point, you'll find happiness too.

1253
01:36:13,777 --> 01:36:16,019
I feel like I'm always searching.

1254
01:36:16,755 --> 01:36:19,582
For something. Someone.

1255
01:36:31,194 --> 01:36:34,206
I feel like I do wanna go to one more bridal fair.

1256
01:36:34,352 --> 01:36:35,640
They're all the same.

1257
01:36:35,768 --> 01:36:38,103
A Shinto wedding sure sounds nice too.

1258
01:36:38,128 --> 01:36:40,209
You said you wanted to be married in a chapel!

1259
01:36:40,724 --> 01:36:42,195
Oh! That reminds me, Teshi.

1260
01:36:42,555 --> 01:36:45,154
Would ya please shave before the ceremony?

1261
01:36:45,263 --> 01:36:47,051
I'm going on a diet for it, ya know?

1262
01:36:47,441 --> 01:36:49,461
She says as she's eating a cake.

1263
01:36:49,595 --> 01:36:51,119
I'll get serious tomorrow.

1264
01:37:50,412 --> 01:37:52,979
The landscape of a town that's no longer there.

1265
01:37:53,633 --> 01:37:56,880
Why does looking at it make my chest feel so tight?

1266
01:39:17,822 --> 01:39:19,375
I was always searching.

1267
01:39:19,701 --> 01:39:20,707
Searching for...

1268
01:39:22,150 --> 01:39:23,248
...someone!

1269
01:40:20,901 --> 01:40:22,079
Excuse me!

1270
01:40:22,490 --> 01:40:23,410
Haven't we...?

1271
01:40:24,117 --> 01:40:26,387
Have I met you somewhere?

1272
01:40:35,332 --> 01:40:36,679
I thought so too!

1273
01:40:41,423 --> 01:40:43,936
Can I ask you... your name?

